metadata.name: Urbanscape #114
metadata.description:
Based on my daily programming routine, I decided to explore urban planning and its structures, so this work is an exploration of city blocks and urban centers. 

Many of the color palettes are taken from architectural and urban diagrams so that the structure of the work is closer to the presentation of architectural sheets. A variety of structures are considered as variations, from close-ups of large blocks and railroad blocks to very small urban structures.

metadata.name: Urbanscape - Genuary Edition #165
metadata.description:
As the last day of January and the beginning of the fxhash festival, with regard to the theme of genuary 31 and inspired by my last work and making changes to it, I decided to present a more complex version of urban structures with many changes in it, So the structure of urban blocks, lights and atmospheres and other important things have been changed. Therefore, this work is a recreated and remixed version of my earlier work with some major changes to achieve a more complex structure and arrangement.

metadata.name: Sketch Block #34
metadata.description:
At the heart of "Sketch Block" is the concept of the sketch block itself - a blank canvas where the possibilities for creation are endless. The name "Sketch Block" reflects the process of creation that inspired the token's design. Like an artist's sketchbook, the token captures the playful experimentation and exploration that underlies the creative process.

The hand-drawn style gives a playful feel to the project, with each shape looking as if it was quickly drawn onto the canvas. Along with the use of vibrant color palettes with tones ranging from soft pastels to bold and bright tones, the projects can produce a wide range of different results.


----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

User Controls:

- Press 'h' to save the image

metadata.name: Tears of the Mountains #70
metadata.description:
The "Tears of the Mountains" is a generative art collection that showcases emotions ranging from tears of happiness to boundless optimism. Inspired by Edgar Payne, I infused my own creative perspective into this art piece, giving consideration to important components such as value, composition, the rule of thirds, and perspective.

This series was crafted with pure code using p5.js.

Created by Costa C. | OneRocket.nft
